relevant_findings.HEENT: Sclera anicteric, mucous membranes moist, oropharynx clear
relevant_findings.neck: Supple, jugular venous pressure not elevated, no lymphadenopathy
relevant_findings.lungs: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no wheezes, rales, or ronchi
relevant_findings.cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, normal S1 and S2, no murmurs, rubs, or gallops
relevant_findings.abdomen: Soft, non-distended, bowel sounds present, no rebound tenderness, slight tenderness to palpation in band across top of abdomen, no right upper quadrant discomfort
relevant_findings.extremities: Warm, well perfused, 2+ pulses, no clubbing, cyanosis, or edema
relevant_findings.neurological: Alert and oriented x 3, no asterixis, tearful but appropriate
